            {
                "id": 1031,
                "name": "Matthias Bussonnier",
                "username": "mbussonnier",
                "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/ask.cyberinfrastructure.org/mbussonnier/{size}/99_2.png",
                "created_at": "2018-10-19T21:04:13.533Z",
                "cooked": "<p>Let me rephrase for schadalapaka here,</p>\n<p>We have a number of users that have a number of jobs using FileIO,  some of them are aware of /dev/shm, and (try to) use it properly. It is annoying as they have to 1) learn about it, 2) clean up after themselves.</p>\n<p>We saw that system.d is mounting /run/user/$(id -u $USER), and tear it down for interactive session, though Slurm job does not seem to trigger it.</p>\n<p>Do you have any experience in hooking something similar into a scheduler so that user have easy access and discoverability while still making sure resources get cleaned up?</p>",
